'''''Mousqueton''''' was one of 20 {{Sclass-|Arquebuse|destroyer}}s built for the [[French Navy]] in the first decade of the 20th century.

On 7 July 1914, ''Mousqueton'' collided with the French Navy [[submarine]] {{ship|French submarine|Calypso|1908|2}} in the [[Mediterranean Sea]] off [[Toulon]], [[France]]. ''Calypso'' sank, but her entire crew of 26 was rescued.<ref>{{Cite newspaper The Times |articlename=French submarine sunk |day_of_week=Wednesday |date=8 July 1914 |page_number=8 |issue=40570 |column=C }}</ref>

